It will be the first time in a club match that Hazard has lined up opposite the Argentine. They previously have played against each other at international level. Hazard dismissed questions about his future at Chelsea, as he enters the last two years on his contact, insisting he is just focused on upcoming matches. Chelsea manager Antonio Conte acknowledged his side will be underdogs in the tie, Barcelona have yet to lose in La Liga this season. He said his team would be excited and that the match would show whether Chelsea are at the level of Europe's elite clubs.
